The paper proposes a filter-based feature selection algorithm for linear SVMs, which is a common machine learning algorithm used in various fields such as natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and artificial intelligence (AI). The algorithm is specifically designed for high dimensional text data sets, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
